text: Compliance Reviews have been rescinded which is explained in the memorandum for PSEP Area Directors and PSEP Territory Managers signed by Kevin Q. McIver dated August 8, 2014. The memo explains the requirement for conducting compliance reviews is rescinded based on a determination

a. redundancy in the activities and documentation related to the risk assessment and compliance review programs. b. sufficient evaluative tools which address the level of compliance with physical security c. no direct impact to current GAO and /or TIGTA audits and subsequent findings and d. no impact to the protection of IRS facilities. Any IRM section that addresses compliance reviews or references to IRM
EFFECT ON OTHER DOCUMENTS This obsoletes IRM 10.2.2 dated May 2, 2013.
